      • isStandardStream

        public static boolean isStandardStream(@NonNull
                                       URL url)
        Returns true if the given URL references the standard input/output streams (that is, if it reads from System.in and writes to System.out). Only one such URL exists: std:/ (see the dsbulk-url module for information on this special url protocol).
        Parameters:
        url - The url to check; must not be null.
        Returns:
        true if the given url has protocol std, false otherwise.
